gold medal-winning 400-meter freestyle relay\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was his first Olympic gold, and he couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t keep the tears from falling.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first Olympic gold\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"the tears\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Phelps, who had won approximately a thousand gold medals to that point, stood next to Dressel laughing and rubbing the 19-year-old\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s head.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.849022638802258e-111, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"approximately a thousand gold medals\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 464}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the 19-year-old\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s head\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Saturday night here, with the kind of poignancy the Olympics tends to produce, Dressel was the beaming veteran soaking up the joy of an eighth gold medal across three different Summer Games.\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"poignancy\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"the beaming veteran\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"the joy\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"an eighth gold medal\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"three different Summer Games\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there was relay mate Hunter Armstrong\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the surprising hero of the night\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094next to him, breaking down, choking up, shedding tears.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"score\": 0.9988971638269589, \"rank\": 0.0005988228311867096, \"text\": \"Hunter\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the night\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094next\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"tears\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This technically was Armstrong\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second career gold medal, but it was his first time standing on the podium (the other gold was as a relay alternate in 2021, which means it was delivered to him in a box days after the event).\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"second career gold medal\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 935}, {\"ngram\": \"his first time\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the other gold\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"a box days\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was now Dressel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s turn to take the Phelps elder statesman role, gently shoving a forearm into Armstong\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s side and laughing.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.34248117497188e-13, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dressel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"elder statesman role\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"a forearm\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"Armstong\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s side\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t explain this moment until you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re on the podium watching the flag go up,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Dressel said.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was really special seeing that.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"really special seeing\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I remember how it was for me, my first gold, I lost it.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s special being part of that with these guys.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d This was a powerful moment for all four American men, who won their country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first gold of the Paris Olympics and helped refute the narrative that U.S. swimming is in decline.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998553257787, \"rank\": 7.394071909780494e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"these guys.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful moment\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"first gold\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"the narrative\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. swimming\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"decline\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They all came to this race in varying stages of their careers, with Dressel having traveled the most publicly challenging road.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this race\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"varying stages\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"their careers\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1745}, {\"ngram\": \"the most publicly challenging road\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thirteen months ago to the day, it seemed highly improbable that Dressel would be back in this place, adding another layer to his legacy as one of the all-time great American Olympians.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998553257787, \"rank\": 7.394071909780494e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"this place\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"another layer\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"his legacy\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d finished 29th in the 100 freestyle at U.S. national championships, a humbling performance for the American record holder in the event.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2030, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_USA_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999848756731401, \"rank\": 1.5120580748361465e-05, \"text\": \"U.S. national championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_USA_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_USA_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998553257787, \"rank\": 7.394071909780494e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100 freestyle\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2026}, {\"ngram\": \"a humbling performance\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was attempting to come back from a breakdown at the 2022 World Championships, which he abruptly left after winning two events with what was described as a mental health issue.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a breakdown\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2174}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 World Championships\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"two events\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"a mental health issue\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thejourney back went through that performance last summer, when Dressel at last returned to high-level competition but wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t up to making the U.S. team for the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009923 worlds.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thejourney\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2317}, {\"ngram\": \"that performance\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"high-level competition\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2421}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. team\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009923 worlds\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that laid the foundation for the summer of 2024, in which Dressel made the Olympic team in two individual events and this relay.\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the foundation\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2527}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic team\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"two individual events\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"this relay\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to win this gold medal, Dressel needed huge performances from his relay mates.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this gold medal\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"huge performances\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"his relay mates\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After years of leading off American relays, the coaches moved Dressel to the anchor for this one and it worked out, with the help of his friends.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://