ticipated mixed bag\", \"from\": 7113, \"to\": 7138}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 7143, \"to\": 7151}, {\"ngram\": \"sizzling butterfly semifinals\", \"from\": 7165, \"to\": 7194}, {\"ngram\": \"the tandem\", \"from\": 7198, \"to\": 7208}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thenlegend Katie Ledeckywon a bronze medal in the 400 freestyle, easily outdistanced by Australian world-record holder Ariarne Titmus and Canadian teenager Summer McIntosh.\\u00c2 For Ledecky, finishing third behind two fellow superstars was probably less disappointing than the time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094she did not break four minutes for the first time in a major international final.\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7332, \"end\": 7342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9983030324260979, \"rank\": 0.001660197140330795, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 7363, \"end\": 7377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 7382, \"end\": 7390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999997911045503, \"rank\": 2.0886546858483397e-07, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thenlegend Katie\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7260}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze medal\", \"from\": 7272, \"to\": 7286}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400 freestyle\", \"from\": 7290, \"to\": 7307}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 7416, \"to\": 7417}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 7422, \"to\": 7429}, {\"ngram\": \"two fellow superstars\", \"from\": 7454, \"to\": 7475}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094she\", \"from\": 7513, \"to\": 7527}, {\"ngram\": \"four minutes\", \"from\": 7542, \"to\": 7554}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 7559, \"to\": 7573}, {\"ngram\": \"a major international final\", \"from\": 7577, \"to\": 7604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI wanted to be a little faster,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 7607, \"to\": 7658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\", \"from\": 7607, \"to\": 7611}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 7645, \"to\": 7652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut I can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t complain with the medal.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The silver medal came in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400 freestyle relay, with the back half of the lineup turning in the heroics.\", \"from\": 7659, \"to\": 7821, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medal.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 7690, \"to\": 7703}, {\"ngram\": \"The silver medal\", \"from\": 7704, \"to\": 7720}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400 freestyle relay\", \"from\": 7729, \"to\": 7762}, {\"ngram\": \"the back half\", \"from\": 7769, \"to\": 7782}, {\"ngram\": \"the lineup\", \"from\": 7786, \"to\": 7796}, {\"ngram\": \"the heroics\", \"from\": 7808, \"to\": 7819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans were in fourth after leadoff swimmer Kate Douglass and second leg Walsh, then Huske turned on the jets to split a 52.06\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094second-fastest of anyone in the race\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094to move the U.S. to second.\", \"from\": 7822, \"to\": 8024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7822, \"end\": 7835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9050873828393693e-28, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 7873, \"end\": 7886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"leadoff swimmer\", \"from\": 7857, \"to\": 7872}, {\"ngram\": \"second leg Walsh\", \"from\": 7891, \"to\": 7907}, {\"ngram\": \"Huske\", \"from\": 7914, \"to\": 7919}, {\"ngram\": \"the jets\", \"from\": 7930, \"to\": 7938}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 7976, \"to\": 7982}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094to\", \"from\": 7986, \"to\": 7999}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 8005, \"to\": 8013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t last long, though.\", \"from\": 8026, \"to\": 8058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It appeared that American anchor Simone Manuel wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be able to hold on to silver, as China surged past on the anchor leg.\", \"from\": 8059, \"to\": 8186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8150, \"end\": 8155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999209220868381, \"rank\": 7.742308228870002e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 8139, \"to\": 8145}, {\"ngram\": \"the anchor leg\", \"from\": 8171, \"to\": 8185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Manuel did what she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s done so often, digging in on the final meters and windmilling one final arm stroke to out-touch China for silver by a tenth of a second.\", \"from\": 8187, \"to\": 8351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8191, \"end\": 8197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_of_Portugal\", \"score\": 0.994032285087486, \"rank\": 0.0032540356510157215, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_of_Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_of_Portugal\"}, {\"begin\": 8311, \"end\": 8316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999209220868381, \"rank\": 7.742308228870002e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 8207, \"to\": 8214}, {\"ngram\": \"the final meters\", \"from\": 8244, \"to\": 8260}, {\"ngram\": \"one final arm\", \"from\": 8277, \"to\": 8290}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 8321, \"to\": 8327}, {\"ngram\": \"a tenth\", \"from\": 8331, \"to\": 8338}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 8342, \"to\": 8350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The time of 3:30.20 broke the American record.\", \"from\": 8352, \"to\": 8398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8382, \"end\": 8390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998553257787, \"rank\": 7.394071909780494e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The time\", \"from\": 8352, \"to\": 8360}, {\"ngram\": \"3:30.20\", \"from\": 8364, \"to\": 8371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt just feels good to be back here, honestly,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Manuel, who like Dresselwent through her own period of several months away from swimming, questioning whether she wanted to keep going.\", \"from\": 8400, \"to\": 8592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8457, \"end\": 8463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_of_Portugal\", \"score\": 0.994032285087486, \"rank\": 0.0032540356510157215, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5